  <div id="accuracy-view" class="chart-view active">
    <h2>Most & Least Accurate Flavors</h2>
    <p>How well did each chip flavor represent what it claimed to be?</p>
    <div class="chart-container">
      <svg id="accuracy-chart" width="100%" height="400"></svg>
    </div>
    <div class="insight-box">
      <h3>Key Insights:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li class="list-item"><span class="key-point">Pesto (Tantos)</span> was rated as the most accurate flavor representation with an average score of 87/100.</li>
        <li class="list-item"><span class="key-point">Scallops (Lay's)</span> was rated as the least accurate with only 24/100.</li>
        <li class="list-item">Most participants agreed that <span class="brand-name">Tantos</span> and <span class="brand-name">Carolina Kettle</span> brands had the most accurate flavor profiles.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div id="enjoyment-view" class="chart-view">
    <h2>Most & Least Enjoyed Flavors</h2>
    <p>Which flavors did participants actually like the most?</p>
    <div class="chart-container">
      <svg id="enjoyment-chart" width="100%" height="400"></svg>
    </div>
    <div class="insight-box">
      <h3>Key Insights:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li class="list-item"><span class="key-point">Salt & Pepper (Trader Joe's)</span> was the most enjoyed flavor with an average score of 80/100.</li>
        <li class="list-item"><span class="key-point">Garlic Shrimp (Doritos)</span> was the least enjoyed with only 19/100.</li>
        <li class="list-item">Three of the top five most enjoyed flavors were from specialty brands rather than mainstream chip companies.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div id="dame-view" class="chart-view">
    <h2>Dame's Favorites & Least Favorites</h2>
    <div class="chart-container">
